ENTRY            A0426   20251207   20260317   20260317       A129
SUBENT        A0426001   20251207   20260317   20260317       A129
BIB                 12         32
TITLE      Proton capture cross section of Sr isotopes and their
           importance for nucleosynthesis of proton-rich nuclides
AUTHOR     (Gy.Gyurky, E.Somorjai, Zs.Fulop, S.Harissopulos,
           P.Demetriou, T.Rauscher)
REFERENCE  (J,PR/C,64,065803,2001)
           (J,NP/A,688,90,2001) Preliminary.
INSTITUTE  (3HUNDEB,2GRCATH,2SWTBAS)
FACILITY   (VDG,3HUNDEB)
SAMPLE     Natural Sr-F/2 targets evaporated onto thick carbon
           backings were used. The number of target atoms was
           determined by proton induced X-Ray emission. The
           results were checked by Rutherford backscattering of
           alpha particles.
MONITOR    (38-SR-0(P,EL)38-SR-0,,DA)
DETECTOR   (SIBAR) To detect the backscattered protons and this
           way to monitor the target stability.
           (HPGE) To detect gamma-rays of produced isotopes.
METHOD     (ACTIV,BCINT,SITA)
           (ACTIV) The irradiations lasted between 6 and 24 hours
           with a beam current of typically 5 -10 mA.
           (GSPEC) The gamma spectra were taken for at least 48
           hours.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No information about source of uncertainty
ADD-RES    (COMP) With calculations "Non-Smoker" and "Most" codes
           astrophysical reaction rates derived from new data
           S-factor is given on figs 6, 7.
HISTORY    (20020708C)
           (20021217U) Last checking has been done.
           (20120120A) NDS(VZ): REL-REF: ND/B->NDS in 002,003,005,
                       006,008.
           (20251207A) SD: Corrections in all Subents.
           Subents 009-011 deleted (see ADD-RES). ERR-T->DATA-ERR.
ENDBIB              32
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           35
SUBENT        A0426002   20251207   20260317   20260317       A129
BIB                  7         14
